<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>CodeCritique</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <header>
        <div class="header">
          <div class="brand">
            <h1>CodeCritique</h1>
            <p>Paste code, run analysis, get metrics + a risk classification.</p>
          </div>

          <span class="badge">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Try something with nested ifs, long functions, or <code>eval()</code>
          </span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <% if (typeof error !== "undefined" && error) { %>
        <div class="alert"><%= error %></div>
        <div style="height: 12px;"></div>
      <% } %>

      <main>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="cardBody">
            <form method="POST" action="/analyze" class="grid">
              <div>
                <label for="code">Submitted code</label>
                <textarea
                  id="code"
                  name="code"
                  placeholder="Paste your code here..."
                  spellcheck="false"
                  autocomplete="off"
                  autocapitalize="off"
                ></textarea>
              </div>

              <div class="row">
                <div>
                  <label for="language">Language</label><br />
                  <select id="language" name="language">
                    <option value="python" selected>Python</option>
                    <option value="javascript">JavaScript (basic scan)</option>
                  </select>
                </div>

                <button class="btn" type="submit">Analyze</button>
                <a class="btn secondary" href="/">Reset</a>

                <span class="muted" style="margin-left:auto;">
                  The analyzer runs on a separate Python service.
                </span>
              </div>
            </form>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="height: 14px;"></div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="cardBody">
            <div class="sectionTitle">
              <h2>What you’ll get</h2>
              <span class="muted">in one run</span>
            </div>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Summary:</strong> risk score + risk level</li>
              <li><strong>Metrics:</strong> LOC, nesting depth, branching points, etc.</li>
              <li><strong>Findings:</strong> security + maintainability flags with explanations</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="height: 14px;"></div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="cardBody">
            <div class="sectionTitle">
              <h2>ML Transition Foundation</h2>
              <span class="muted">week 6 focus</span>
            </div>

            <ul class="list">
              <li><strong>Feature extraction:</strong> the analyzer now exposes the same feature vector used for model training.</li>
              <li><strong>Rule-first scoring:</strong> the current demo still uses rule-based scoring as the main result.</li>
              <li><strong>Model support:</strong> ML predictions are shown for comparison while the dataset and feature set mature.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>

      <footer style="margin-top: 18px;">
        <p class="muted" style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
          &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> uche oranye Code Critique. All rights reserved.
        </p>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
